backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528378\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104huu1665702982941.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/huu1665702982941.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/huu1665702982941.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"huu1665702982941\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Secondary Process Character Mnemonics\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">These mnemonics define the character used in a secondary process, for example, for printers which must print a line twice to produce an underline. This technique is also used with some display devices.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"huu1665702982941__section_rl2_ctp_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d391251e51\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__1\">Mnemonic </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__2\">Default </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__3\">Explanation </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_underscore</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__2\">_ </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__3\">Character used with _underscore. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_inverse</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__2\">. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"huu1665702982941__table_d5639e1_d5640e1_d5641e1__entry__3\">Character used with _inverse. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"huu1665702982941__section_mb5_ftp_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d391251e121\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"huu1665702982941__p_d64274e1_d64275e1_d64276e1\">If the <code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_inverse</code> mnemonic is not\n        defined, only spaces in inverse text are filled with a period (.). If the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_inverse</code> mnemonic is defined, the specified character is printed\n        over each inverse position.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"huu1665702982941__p_d64277e1_d64278e1_d64279e1\">If you define any of the color mnemonics (that is,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">color, color_n, _color</code>, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">_color_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>) in the device section, any definition for <code class=\"ph codeph\">_inverse</code> is\n        ignored. This also means that <code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_inverse</code> is ignored.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"huu1665702982941__p_d64280e1_d64281e1_d64282e1\">The following example shows the definition used in the\n        standard HP2645 translation table:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"huu1665702982941__pre_kyc_htp_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^BEGIN_SET 0\n^NUL ^SELECT\n...\n_ ^PRINTER_UNDERSCORE\n...\n^END_SET\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gox1665702984604.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Index Color Mnemonics</a><p>Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bbb1665702981995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Secondary Process Color and Video Mnemonics</a><p>The secondary process mnemonics instruct Uniface to perform the video feature in a secondary print or display process, that is, by printing the line a second time.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528378\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528378\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Secondary Process Character Mnemonics Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Secondary Process Character Mnemonics These mnemonics define the character used in a secondary process, for example, for printers which must print a line twice to produce an underline. This technique is also used with some display devices. Arguments Mnemonic Default Explanation printer_underscore _ Character used with _underscore. printer_inverse . Character used with _inverse. Description If the printer_inverse mnemonic is not defined, only spaces in inverse text are filled with a period (.). If the printer_inverse mnemonic is defined, the specified character is printed over each inverse position. If you define any of the color mnemonics (that is, color, color_n, _color , or _color_ n ) in the device section, any definition for _inverse is ignored. This also means that printer_inverse is ignored. The following example shows the definition used in the standard HP2645 translation table: ^BEGIN_SET 0 ^NUL ^SELECT ... _ ^PRINTER_UNDERSCORE ... ^END_SET Copy Related Links Uniface Index Color Mnemonics Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations. Secondary Process Color and Video Mnemonics The secondary process mnemonics instruct Uniface to perform the video feature in a secondary print or display process, that is, by printing the line a second time. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}